On March 23, 2018, the President signed into law several bills designating various facilities of the United States Postal Service with specific names. These include the Janet Capello Post Office Building, the Dr. John F. Nash, Jr. Post Office, the John Fitzgerald Kennedy Post Office, the Sgt. Douglas J. Riney Post Office, the Gunnery Sergeant John Basilone Post Office, the Staff Sergeant Peter Taub Post Office Building, the Sr. Chief Ryan Owens Post Office Building, the Howard B. Pate, Jr. Post Office, the Rutledge Pearson Post Office Building, the Dr. Walter S. McAfee Post Office Building, the Zack T. Addington Post Office, the Robert H. Jenkins, Jr. Post Office, the Borinqueneers Post Office Building, and the James C. 'Billy' Johnson Post Office Building.